We are reiterating our recommendations in the CY 2014 Annual Audit Report, to wit:

a.	Submit a written explanation/justification on the importance of the attendance of the officials to the said Lakbay-Aral and evidence of invitation or approval from the host LGU and DILG;

b.	Submit evidence that LGU-Marihatag was a contingent/participant during the Sinulog 2014 Festival, such as, but not limited to, program of activity showing the Municipality as a contingent and the City of Cebu’s certification on its participation;

c.	Observe the austerity measures set by proper authority, minimize attendance to Lakbay Aral and instead, appropriate Agency funds for projects/activities that brings immediate socio-economic benefits among local constituents; and

d.	Observe strictly the guidelines on the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances under COA Memorandum Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997.
